{"word":"Nineveh","slug":"nineveh","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Nineveh</b> <a href=\"#/H5210\">H5210</a> <br/> Capital of the Assyrian empire<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=10&verse=12'>Gen 10:12</a><br/> Contained a population of upwards of one hundred and twenty thousand when Jonah preached<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=32&chapter=4&verse=11'>Jon 4:11</a><br/> Extent of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=32&chapter=3&verse=4'>Jon 3:4</a><br/> Sennacherib in<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=19&verse=37'>2Ki 19:37</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=23&chapter=37&verse=38'>Isa 37:38</a><br/> Jonah preaches to<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=32&chapter=1&verse=2'>Jon 1:2</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=32&chapter=3&verse=10'>Jon 3:10</a><br/> Nahum prophesies against<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=34&chapter=1'>Nah 1</a><br/> Zephaniah foretells the desolation of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=36&chapter=2&verse=15'>Zep 2:15</a>"}]}